45    /**
46    * A parser/interpreter for an RDF graph which represents an OWL ontology. The
47    * consumer interprets triple patterns in the graph to produce the appropriate
48    * OWLAPI entities, class expressions and axioms. The parser is based on triple
49    * handlers. A given triple handler handles a specific type of triple. Generally
50    * speaking this is based on the predicate of a triple, for example, A
51    * rdfs:subClassOf B is handled by a subClassOf handler. A handler determines if
52    * it can handle a triple in a streaming mode (i.e. while parsing is taking
53    * place) or if it can handle a triple after parsing has taken place and the
54    * complete graph is in memory. Once a handler handles a triple, that triple is
55    * deemed to have been consumed an is discarded. The parser attempts to consume
56    * as many triples as possible while streaming parsing is taking place. Whether
57    * or not a triple can be consumed during parsing is determined by installed
58    * triple handlers.
59    *
60    * @author Matthew Horridge, The University Of Manchester, Bio-Health
61    * Informatics Group
62    * @since 2.0.0
63    */
